The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Glimpses of life

 Capturing for eternity the myriad moods and flavours of life in the space of a flickering instant, photographs tell stories worth a thousand words. Still and silent, they are capable of arousing thoughts, feelings and sensations encompassing the entire gamut of our emotions. Hosted by Photographic Association of Dum Dum, the 48th International Exhibition of Photographic Art has on show 91 such photographs (31 monochrome and 60 colour), offering an irresistible visual treat for photography enthusiasts and those with a taste for the aesthetic. Featuring works by 71 master lensmen of 25 countries including England, France, Germany, USA, Japan, Sweden, Greece, Canada, Hong Kong and Vietnam, it celebrates the triumph of human life over all odds and the undying spirit of faith and optimism it stands for.

 Event: An international photographic exhibition

 When: Till October 23, 5 pm - 9 pm

 Where: Dum Dum Motijheel College




